OL,3,CManchester's development plans
OL,4,Ccriticised for inaccessibility
OL,6,FDevelopments in Manchester's Stevenson
OL,7,FSquare have been criticised by
OL,8,Fdisability activists.
OL,10,FThe plans were for an area that was
OL,11,Fpartly pedestrianised, with outdoor
OL,12,Fseating and cycle lanes. Manchester
OL,13,FCity Council described it as "a safe
OL,14,Fspace to move through."
OL,16,FDave Steele has tunnel vision and has
OL,17,Fbeen losing his sight for the last ten
OL,18,Fyears and has found concrete blocks
OL,19,Fplaced around the area as inaccessible.
