OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F398A1706661383
OL,3,CManchester's development plans
OL,4,Ccriticised for inaccessibility
OL,6,F"These have been placed to make the
OL,7,Fplace look pretty or places for people
OL,8,Fto sit, but they are the perfect
OL,9,Fheight for anyone, not just people
OL,10,Flike me with a visual impairment to
OL,11,Fhit their shins on," said Mr Steele.
OL,13,F"Unless my cane hits that, which I'm
OL,14,Fhoping it's going to, I'm maybe going
OL,15,Fto trip over them and they are dotted
OL,16,Feverywhere."
OL,18,FAnother concern for visually impaired
OL,19,Fpeople is the lack of indicators to
OL,20,Fhelp when crossing the road.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G2/7
