OL,3,CManchester's development plans
OL,4,Ccriticised for inaccessibility
OL,6,F"Normally I'd be looking for a
OL,7,Fspinning cone, which that one's not
OL,8,Fthere," continued Mr Steele.
OL,10,F"If someone's trying to get across
OL,11,Fwith a wheelchair, or who's got
OL,12,Fmobility issues, they'd be struggling
OL,13,Fto get across in time. There's no
OL,14,Faudio whatsoever, so you're really
OL,15,Fstruggling. You're not going to get
OL,16,Facross safely."
OL,18,FCampaigners are asking for those with
OL,19,Fdisabilities to be consulted when it
OL,20,Fcomes to these shared spaces.
